text.tspan: Mean income per year within the poorest decile (after tax), 1963 to 2024
The mean income per year within the poorest decile (tenth of the population). This data is adjusted for inflation
and differences in living costs between countries. Income here is measured after taxes and benefits.

Note: This data is expressed in
international-$
at 2021 prices.
